title: Crab Stuffed Shrimp
summary: Crab Stuffed Shrimp might be just the hor d'oeuvre you are searching for. One serving contains 123 calories, 13g of protein, and 4g of fat. For $2.44 per serving, this recipe covers 24% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe serves 1. 8 people have made this recipe and would make it again. It is a good option if you're following a dairy free and pescatarian diet. Head to the store and pick up country mustard, parsley, green onion, and a few other things to make it today. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 45 minutes. With a spoonacular score of 92%, this dish is outstanding. Try Crab Stuffed Shrimp, Crab & Shrimp Stuffed Sole, and Jalapeno and Crab Stuffed Shrimp for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Riesling, and Sauvignon Blanc are my top picks for Shrimp. These crisp white wines work well with shrimp prepared in a variety of ways, whether grilled, fried, or in garlic sauce. The Maso Canali Pinot Grigio with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 15 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Maso Canali Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: The Maso Canali Pinot Grigio displays a brilliant pale golden color indicative of its crisp, citrus aromas and floral notes. This wine is well-balanced and full-flavored with hints of nectarine. Pair it with seafood and light poultry for a delightful meal.

instructions: First make the crab mixture. Mix all ingredients togethermix should not be wet and should hold its shape. Set aside. Heat oil in a skillet, saut vegetables and season with salt and pepper, top with slivered almonds. Set aside. Butterfly the tail of the shrimp, add some crab mix on the bottom and top of the shrimp and sprinkle toasted panko on top and bake in the oven at 350-400 until done. Serve on top of mixed vegetables.First make the crab mixture. Mix all ingredients togethermix should not be wet and should hold its shape. Set aside.
